		Aalto Global Impact is currently seeking a full-time intern to work with us on our ongoing projects and activities, starting from the 2nd of January 2013 (for 3-5 months). The internship will be based at Aalto University, School of Business (Lapuankatu 2). The successful candidate will work closely with the AGI team members, as well as our partners, on the implementation of the ongoing projects.<br><br>Specific tasks of the internship include:<br>- Administrative support to the AGI team members<br>- Participate in / take minutes of meetings<br>- Communicate with partners regarding ongoing issues<br>- Working with social media and other communication channels<br>- Participation in / and organizing of events<br>- Other tasks related to AGIâ€™s activities.<br><br>Qualifications and requirements:<br>- Experience with volunteering, community organizing, and/or event planning<br>- Experience and interest in working with the administrative office or project tasks<br>- Well organized, able to multitask efficiently, and attention to detail<br>- Experienced in using Microsoft Office, Internet, social media and other office applications and machines<br>- Self-motivated and able to work both independently and within teams<br>- Interest in sustainable development, societal impact and global responsibility issues<br>- Strong interpersonal, oral, and written communication skills in Finnish and English, knowledge of other languages are an asset<br>- Positive attitude and commitment to improvement to high levels of professionalism.<br><br>Aalto Global Impact will offer a monthly stipend of EUR 1100 a month.<br><br>How to apply:<br>To apply for this internship, submit your CV with an accompanying cover letter, explaining your specific interest in this position by email to info@aaltoglobalimpact.org before the 12th of November 2012, 12:00.<br>All applicants will be notified about the status of their application by the end of November.<br>
